name: Medusae - Rhopilema Nomadica
description: What can jellyfish teach us about climate change? Warming of temperatures, oxygen depletion and ocean acidification, coupled with overfishing and invasive species, are giving jellyfish advantage over other marine life. Rhopilema Nomadica, or nomad jellyfish, is listed as one of the worst invasive marine species in European waters.Half of the profit made with this series Medusae will be donated to WWF Mediterranean to help protect the Mediterranean Sea.
